<div id="review_4262230678" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4262230678" />
    <a title="Vince" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/128225739-vince"><img alt="Vince" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629724401p2/128225739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4262230678?book_show_action=true">Oct 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vince" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vince" href="/user/show/128225739-vince">Vince</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4262230678" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18363000614150610879">Quite a unique novel. It&apos;s an alternate world in Alaska and I love alternate worlds. It took me a couple of a hundred pages to get into this book but once it took off, I was hooked. Michael Chabon may become another favorite author to go along my long list. I loved the noir style storytelling and the characters captured my attention and guided me through the story. There were a lot of Yiddish phrases that went over my head and I suck at solving mysteries in stories and I&apos;m still confused on how </span>
  <span id="freeText18363000614150610879" style="display:none">Quite a unique novel. It's an alternate world in Alaska and I love alternate worlds. It took me a couple of a hundred pages to get into this book but once it took off, I was hooked. Michael Chabon may become another favorite author to go along my long list. I loved the noir style storytelling and the characters captured my attention and guided me through the story. There were a lot of Yiddish phrases that went over my head and I suck at solving mysteries in stories and I'm still confused on how it all turned out in the end. But regardless, I can definitely say that I enjoyed my time reading it.I don't think I've read a novel quite like this and a part of me hopes I never do again because I want the unique experience of reading this book to last forever. A solid 4 out of 5</span>
  <a data-text-id="18363000614150610879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
